    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="12"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2114.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-12-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 23, 1867.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your dispatch of the 6th of December, No. 1489,
                    has been received. I approve of the manner in which you have carried out the <pb
                        facs="0178" n="130" xml:id="pg_130"/> instructions in my 2087. At the same
                    time, I observe with regret that Lord Stanley has not found it convenient to
                    indicate any practical way of removing the difficulties thus brought to his
                    notice.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
